OL,3,CChildren's autism diagnoses in Jersey
OL,4,Crise year-on-year since 2020
OL,6,FJersey residents want more specialist
OL,7,Feducational support on the island
OL,8,Fafter an ITV Freedom of Information
OL,9,Frequest revealed autism diagnoses for
OL,10,Fchildren and young people are rising
OL,11,Fyear after year.
OL,13,FThe FoI found that 28 children and
OL,14,Fyoung people were diagnosed with
OL,15,Fautism in 2020, with 71 children
OL,16,Fdiagnosed already as of August 2024.
OL,18,FThere are currently three mainstream
OL,19,Fsecondary and three primary schools in
OL,20,FJersey which help those with special
OL,21,Feducational needs.
